    "caption": "Every flower, every fruit, depends on this little flier.",
    "shortDescription": "Bees pollinate about a third of all the food humans eat — without bees visiting flowers and spreading pollen, most of our fruits and vegetables wouldn't exist. When a honeybee finds a great patch of flowers, it flies back to the hive and performs a waggle dance to tell the other bees exactly where to go. Fun fact: A single honeybee produces only about one twelfth of a teaspoon of honey in its entire lifetime."
